home.name: Social
home.content: Currently, we have one running and active project, namely, Project Prithvi. Project Prithvi aims to reduce the consumption of plastic in everyday items and replace it with alternate eco-friendly and made in India products and materials. We also aim to popularize the idea of using such products and positively influence people to use eco-friendly and made in India products. For this, we have partnered with other organizations like Bamboo India and Shetastic Pvt. Ltd., who work on similar principles. Through Project Prithvi, we also ensure and help small farmers, MSME workers and other people on our project with employment oppurtunities.

home.name: Entrepreneurship
home.content: We are Enactus S.P.I.T., the student chapter of Enactus India at Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan's Sardar Patel Institute of Technology, Mumbai. We, at Enactus S.P.I.T., are a team of passionate students dedicated in developing a new generation of socially responsible leaders. We believe in having the perspective to see an opportunity and the talent to create value from that opportunity. We aspire to impact as many lives as we can and create sustainable growth for this world to prosper with opportunities for all. Through the community outreach projects undertaken by us, we impact, influence and bring about formidable changes in the society to empower & enourage those in need through our knowledge, experience and creativity that we build over time.

home.name: Cause
home.content: You might have heard of reusing and recycling plastic waste. But toothbrushes are never considered a part of waste. They are rather dumped in the garbage, making it more difficult to find and reuse/recycle them. This contibutes to further production of plastic toothbrushes, increasing the volume of this harmful substance. We are promoting one hundred percent eco-friendly products ranging from daily use items (like bamboo toothbrushes & cotton masks) to decorative and artistic articles. By exchanging your plastic product to bamboo/cotton one, you would be contributing to our mission of reducing plastic and saving our environment. Looking forward to your participation in our initiative of saving our environment!! You can checkout our products on our website or contact us.

leadership.name: Dr. Rita Das
leadership.description: Our CEO, Peter, credits his hardworking East Asian immigrant parents who undertook the arduous journey to the shores of America with the intention of giving their children the best future. His mother's wizardy in the kitchen whipping up the tastiest dishes with whatever is available inexpensively at the supermarket, was his first inspiration to create the fusion cuisines for which The Frying Pan became well known. He brings his zeal for fusion cuisines to this restaurant, pioneering cross-cultural culinary connections.

leadership.name: Rani Tibdewal
leadership.description: Our CFO, Danny, as he is affectionately referred to by his colleagues, comes from a long established family tradition in farming and produce. His experiences growing up on a farm in the Australian outback gave him great appreciation for varieties of food sources. As he puts it in his own words, Everything that runs, wins, and everything that stays, pays!

leadership.name: Shobhit Verma
leadership.description: Blessed with the most discerning gustatory sense, Agumbe, our CFO, personally ensures that every dish that we serve meets his exacting tastes. Our chefs dread the tongue lashing that ensues if their dish does not meet his exacting standards. He lives by his motto, You click only if you survive my lick.

leadership.name: Akash Junnarkar
leadership.description: Award winning three-star Michelin chef with wide International experience having worked closely with whos-who in the culinary world, he specializes in creating mouthwatering Indo-Italian fusion experiences. He says, Put together the cuisines from the two craziest cultures, and you get a winning hit! Amma Mia!
